---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import { SITE_TITLE } from '../consts';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead
			title={`About | ${SITE_TITLE}`}
			description="About the Building Wayfinder engineering blog"
		/>
		<style>
			.about {
				max-width: 680px;
				margin: 0 auto;
			}
		</style>
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />
		<main>
			<div class="about">
				<h1>About This Blog</h1>
				<p>
					<strong>Building Wayfinder</strong> is a technical engineering blog documenting the
					real-time build of Wayfinder, a personalized travel companion app for iOS.
				</p>

				<h2>What is Wayfinder?</h2>
				<p>
					Wayfinder is a context-aware travel companion that adapts to your preferences,
					location, and surroundings to deliver relevant recommendations throughout your journey.
					It combines structured user preferences with semantic search (pgvector), LLM-powered
					re-ranking (Claude), and real-time context signals like location, weather, and time of day.
				</p>

				<h2>What is Project OS?</h2>
				<p>
					Every feature of Wayfinder is built using Project OS, a structured development workflow
					that uses specialist AI agents for spec writing, architecture, building, code review, and
					QA. This blog documents both the app itself and the methodology used to build it.
				</p>

				<h2>The Stack</h2>
				<ul>
					<li><strong>iOS:</strong> SwiftUI + SwiftData</li>
					<li><strong>Backend:</strong> Bun + Hono + Drizzle ORM</li>
					<li><strong>Database:</strong> Postgres + pgvector</li>
					<li><strong>AI:</strong> Claude (chat + re-ranking) + Voyage (embeddings)</li>
					<li><strong>Maps:</strong> Overture Maps + Apple MapKit</li>
				</ul>

				<h2>Who</h2>
				<p>
					Built by a solo developer using Claude Code with the Project OS methodology.
					Follow along as we go from zero to App Store.
				</p>
			</div>
		</main>
		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>
